2500|$|Niger – In January 2012, President Mahamadou Issoufou {{said that}} Niger will {{continue}} with its plans <b>to</b> <b>build</b> <b>a</b> civilian <b>nuclear</b> {{power plant in}} cooperation with other West African countries in the ECOWAS, rather than letting the Chernobyl and Fukushima disasters make Niger cancel its plans. He also stated that [...] "In addition to renewable energy, nuclear energy is clean and low cost".|$|R
